%N A082586 Length of the run of consecutive equal digits in the decimal expansion of Pi beginning at position n and ignoring any immediately-previous equal digits.
%C A082586 Digits 3,1,4,... are indexed 1,2,3,...
%e A082586 Pi = 3.141592653589793238462643383279502884... and the first run of 2 starts at position 25, so a(n) = 1 for n < 25, a(25) = 2.
%e A082586 Runs of length 2 begin in positions 25,35,45,60,80,95 then not again until 118. Compare A049514 and A049518.
